{"id": "1429993038297432124", "channel_id": "1429993038297432124", "type": 0, "author_id": "452609886170251265", "author_name": "tksn.", "author_bot": false, "content": "Hi BIAV, \n\nI think you have already received a lot of feedback regarding Pollux's power level. However, I wanted to focus specifically on some issues with his skills that I think are major problems for him from a design standpoint. Regardless of how powerful he is, I believe these are fundamental issues which affect how he feels to play, meaning that if they are not addressed, he will not feel good to use regardless of how strong he is. Please consider changing or adjusting these parts of his kit.\n\nThere are two important points I want to establish first. These two points are crucial to Pollux's character identity, and I believe it is important for his design to stay consistent with these points. These two points are:\n\n1. Pollux is very similar to Castor, which is clearly very intentional. They are twins, and being similar in design is a good choice to emphasize their similarities. Many of his mechanics are very similar to Castor's mechanics, and they are clearly meant to complement each other when played on the same team.\n\n2. Pollux is very clearly designed as a sustained damage character. His cards all have Retain, his Sin Mark mechanic scales up over time, and Atonement by Pain increases in value for every fight in an exploration. All of this, combined, means that his skill design clearly communicates that he is a sustained damage character who ramps up over time. This means that he does not have the ability to do massive, overwhelming burst damage to one-turn kill a boss. Instead, he should make up for it by having a consistent amount of damage every turn, with some capability to do high damage when set up.\n\nThese are the two core concepts that I believe define Pollux as a character. However, his kit has many flaws which affect his performance with regards to these concepts. Here are the main issues I believe he has:", "timestamp": "2025-10-21T00:41:48.316000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": null, "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [{"emoji": "👍🏿", "emoji_id": null, "count": 21}], "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "reply_to": null, "has_thread": false, "thread_id": "1429993038297432124", "flags": 0, "thread_title": "✅「Answered」Flaws and Weaknesses in Pollux's skill design", "forum_channel_id": "1180845276823564288", "is_thread_starter": true, "thread_tags": ["1181168158678204497", "1361168939622727801"]}
